---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';

const ctaHref = 'mailto:hamish@australianmathcoach.com';
---

<Layout
  title="About Australian Math Coach"
  description="Learn the mission behind Australian Math Coach and why mathematical thinking and problem-solving matter for students in a changing world."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-4">About Australian Math Coach</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-800 font-medium mb-6">Helping students build the thinking skills they need for a changing world.</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Australian Math Coach is focused on mathematical thinking, problem-solving, and confidence with unfamiliar questions. The goal is not just to get through homework. It is to help students understand ideas clearly and apply them with confidence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-5">Why mathematical thinking matters</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          <p>
            Maths is not just calculation. At its best, it develops reasoning, structure, pattern recognition, and problem-solving.
          </p>
          <p>
            As AI becomes more capable, these skills matter even more. Students need to think clearly, ask good questions, explain ideas, and stay confident when a problem is unfamiliar.
          </p>
          <p>
            Technology can produce answers quickly. But students still need to understand <em>why</em> something works and how to evaluate whether an answer makes sense.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-5">About me</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          <p>
            I&apos;m Hamish MacDonald, a senior data platform and engineering consultant, and I work with complex systems that rely on clear logic, structured thinking, and good decision-making.
          </p>
          <p>
            I&apos;m also a father of two school-age children. That personal perspective matters deeply to how I coach: I care about helping students build genuine understanding, not just short-term performance.
          </p>
          <p>
            Australian Math Coach grew from that combination of professional and personal experience: a belief that children do better when they learn how to think, question, and solve problems with confidence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-6">Teaching philosophy</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <article class="rounded-2xl bg-white border border-slate-100 p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Understanding before memorisation</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Students should know why a method works, not only how to repeat it.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-2xl bg-white border border-slate-100 p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Questions before answers</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Strong learning starts with curiosity, clear questions, and thoughtful reasoning.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-2xl bg-white border border-slate-100 p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Problem-solving as a skill</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Students can learn repeatable strategies for tackling unfamiliar and complex problems.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-2xl bg-white border border-slate-100 p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Confidence through guided practice</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Confidence grows when students practise with structure, feedback, and steady challenge.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Start with a free first session"
    description="The first session is a chance to understand your child’s current thinking, goals and whether this style of coaching is a good fit."
    ctaLabel="Book a free session"
    ctaHref={ctaHref}
  />
</Layout>
